---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "June 19, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Flowdira"
  description="How Flowdira collects, uses and protects your personal information when you use our website or engage our design, development and AI integration services."
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main" class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal__lede">
        Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains what information Flowdira
        collects, how we use it, and the choices you have.
      </p>
      <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Flowdira (“we”, “us”, or “our”) operates flowdira.com and provides website
        design, web development and AI integration services. This policy applies to
        information we collect through our website and in the course of providing
        our services.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact details</strong> you provide voluntarily — such as your
          name, email address and project details — when you submit our enquiry
          form or email us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage data</strong> collected automatically, such as your browser
          type, device, pages visited and referring source, gathered through
          analytics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Project information</strong> you share with us so we can deliver
          an engagement, including content, brand assets and access credentials.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your enquiries and provide quotes;</li>
        <li>Deliver, maintain and improve our services;</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about your project;</li>
        <li>Understand how our website is used and improve it;</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookies &amp; analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Our website uses Google Analytics to understand how visitors interact with
        it. These tools may set cookies and collect anonymised usage data such as
        pages visited and approximate location. You can control or block cookies
        through your browser settings; doing so may affect some website
        functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        We rely on trusted third-party platforms to operate our website and deliver
        projects — including hosting and deployment providers such as Vercel and
        Cloudflare, code hosting on GitHub, and AI model providers. These services
        process data under their own privacy policies. We encourage you to review
        their policies where relevant.
      </p>

      <h2>6. How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We only share it with service
        providers who help us operate our website and deliver our services, or where
        required by law. Any such providers are expected to handle your data
        securely and only for the purposes we specify.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the
        purposes described in this policy, to comply with our legal obligations, and
        to resolve disputes. When information is no longer needed, we take steps to
        delete or anonymise it.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct,
        delete or restrict the use of your personal information, and to object to
        certain processing. To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the
        details below.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your
        information against unauthorised access, loss or misuse. However, no method
        of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee
        absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our website and services are not directed at children, and we do not
        knowingly collect personal information from anyone under the age of 16. If
        you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please
        contact us so we can remove it.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The latest version will
        always be available on this page with a revised “last updated” date. We
        encourage you to review it periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any privacy questions or requests, email us at
        <a href="mailto:contact@flowdira.com">contact@flowdira.com</a>.
      </p>

      <a href="/" class="legal__back">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" width="14" height="14">
          <path
            d="M10 12 6 8l4-4"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.7"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        Back to home
      </a>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
